    "7 \"asymptotic\" means that we can ignore lower order polynomials and constants when we describe a function.",
    "For instance, the function f (n) = 4n + n 3 is written as O(n 3), since 4n becomes insignificant compared to n 3 as n increases.",
    "the salad bar leads Φ to the exponential O(2 n).",
    "Even if your gustatory imagination could utilize the speed of the parallelized neural computation of your brain, which allowed you to imagine one billion salads per second, a salad bar of 50 ingredients would still take you 13 days to master, and a bar of 60 takes you roughly 37 billion years.",
